    <div class="container">
    <img src="../assets/images/Seafood-Paella-LEAD-VERTICAL.jpg" alt="Tortilla de patatas" class="image">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="text">This meal is the most iconic Spanish meal. It is served all around Spain and is served in just about any restaurant you walk into. This meal is made in a large pan that is specifically for paella. There are so many different kinds of ways to make this famous dish however the basics consist of rice and seafood with vegetables and possibly other sources of protein.</div>
    </div>
    </div> <!-- end of food class -->
      <div class="container">
    <img src="../assets/images/pan-tumaca.jpg" alt="Tortilla de patatas" class="image">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="text">This dish is served as a breakfast or afternoon snack in Spain. It consists of bread, olive oil, salt, and tomato spread. It is one of the more simple dishes however it is a delightful food to enjoy in Spain during your stay.</div>
    </div>
    </div> <!-- end of food class -->
      <div class="container">
    <img src="../assets/images/meet-ham-slicer.jpg" alt="Tortilla de patatas" class="image">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="text">Just walking down the streets of Madrid you may notice many shops that have dried pork legs surrounding the lining of the store and hanging from their ceilings. This is a very commonly known snack in Madrid. This cured Iberian ham is absolutely delicious and you cannot leave Madrid without trying this delicacy.</div>
    </div>
    </div> <!-- end of food class -->
  </div>
