    <div class="container">
    <img src="../assets/images/IMG_3876.jpg" alt="Tortilla de patatas" class="image">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="text">This perfectly stewed bull’s tail is absolutely done to perfection in Spain. There is no place better to enjoy this dish than to be in the country that is home to the symbolic bull. This is another one of Spain’s more traditional dishes, and while knowing that it is the tail of the bull may turn you off from trying this dish, try it first because you may love it.</div>
    </div>
    </div> <!-- end of food class -->
      <div class="container">
    <img src="../assets/images/IMG_6028.jpg" alt="Tortilla de patatas" class="image">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="text">This food is a soup served cold. Yes, you may be thinking why would soup be cold, but think again as this soup is delightful. It is a Tomato based soup topped with olive oil, bread crumbs, and tastes of creamy garlic. This dish originated from Cordoba but made its way to Madrid for many restaurants to serve.</div>
    </div>
    </div> <!-- end of food class -->
